main event: On 15 March 1965, an unidentified flying object resembling an aircraft was observed in Lincoln, Nebraska.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for about eight seconds., The object appeared to be flying south during the observation., Distinguishing characteristics of the object were not provided., It was later suggested that the sighting could be attributed to a scheduled weather balloon release in the area., The report was part of Project Blue Book, which investigated UFO sightings for the U.S. Air Force.
sighted object: lights that appeared to be aircraft
